cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.HC 

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques to obfuscate identities in photos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graphics and visualization techniques, which makes cs.GR (Computer Graphics) another likely category. Additionally, the paper uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for data-driven image synthesis, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). As the paper deals with privacy risks, it could also be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of its approach for social media, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
